        <profile name="Shock &amp; Disorient" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="a10b-53ca-dd57-1e4c">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After this unit is Activated, if it has Assault Doctrine, until the End step, each enemy unit that not visible to this unit gains the following ability:

Unnerved: For each attack that targets this unit, that attack gains Suppressive X where X is equal to its Damage (or improves Suppressive by X if it already has it).</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Shadow Strike" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="5f45-fe74-cf6a-a370">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After this unit is Activated in reserves, roll 2D6+2. You may ‘strike from the shadows’. If you do, Deploy this unit anywhere on the battlefield at least X” away from all enemy units where X is the result of that roll. If you do, during this turn’s Move step, do not make a Move Roll and this unit cannot Advance or Reposition.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Combat Grapnels" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="6b8c-c01f-0688-0883">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">While this unit’s models move, they may ignore vertical distances.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
    </selectionEntry>
